  • Method Details

    • isEmpty

      default boolean isEmpty()
      Tests if this ImmutableSymbolTable maps no keys to value. In other words, its size is 0.
      Returns:
      true if this ImmutableSymbolTable maps no keys to values; false otherwise.

    • get

      Value get(Key key)
      Retrieve the value for a given key.
      Parameters:
      key - the key.
      Returns:
      the value, if key is present, else null.

    • validateKey

      default void validateKey(Key key)
      Validates the provided key. Throws an IllegalArgumentException if the key is null.
      Parameters:
      key - the key to validate.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the key is null.

    • contains

      default Boolean contains(Key key)
      Determine if this BST contains key.
      Parameters:
      key - the key to find.
      Returns:
      true if this contains key.

    • getOrDefault

      default Value getOrDefault(Key key, Supplier<Value> defaultValueFunction)
      Retrieves the value to which the specified key is mapped, or returns the default value if the key is not found.
      Parameters:
      key - the key whose associated value is to be returned.
      defaultValueFunction - the (call-by-name) default value to return if the specified key is not present in the symbol table.
      Returns:
      the value associated with the specified key, or the provided default value if the key is not present.

    • keys

      Get the size of this ImmutableSymbolTable.

      the current size.
